pageContext.description: Terminal discs are imperfect, & the upper plate of one is missing. Decorated with 5 raised bands divided by roped fillets; the upper plate of the remaining disc is ornamented with knobs encircled by concentric circles, the backs of the discs are ribbed.
pageContext.collection: National Museum of Science & Art, Dublin, Plate VIII, 40, W 20., formerly in the Collection of Dean H.R. Dawson.
